                <h1>Air Canada Heuristic Evaluation </h1>
                <hr class="mt-1 line">
                <h2 class="pt-3 mb-0">Project Directive</h2>
                <p>Assess the usability of Air Canada's mobile application and create a customer journey map for
                    customers:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p class="p-0 m-0">Shopping for flights</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p class="p-0 m-0">Tracking flight of friends and family members</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>The Nielsen Norman Group's <a class="blue"
                        href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/ten-usability-heuristics/" target="blank">10
                        Usability Heuristics for User Interface Design</a> served as the basis for the analysis of
                    the application's usability. Understanding the strength's and shortcomings of common task flows
                    within the application are essential before iterating through wireframes, prototypes, and high
                    fidelity designs.</p>

                <h3 class="pt-3">Booking a Trip</h3>
                <p class="pb-3">The first screens I evaluated were users that needed to book a flight.
                </p>

